CS 4880 - P0
Cynthia

------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Reads whitespace-delimited string tokens from a file or stdin, builds a
binary search tree (BST) ordered by token frequency, and outputs the
tree in three traversals to separate files.

BST ordering: a token that appears more times is "greater" than one that
appears fewer times. Tokens with equal frequency share the same node,
listed in order of first appearance.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
FILES
------------------------------------------------------------------------
P0.c       - main, argument handling, input reading, output orchestration
tree.c     - buildTree, printPreorder, printInorder, printPostorder, free_tree
tree.h     - public function declarations (buildTree, print*, free_tree)
node.h     - Node struct definition
Makefile   - build rules

------------------------------------------------------------------------
BUILD
------------------------------------------------------------------------
make

To clean object files and the executable:
make clean

------------------------------------------------------------------------
INVOCATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Read from keyboard (enter tokens, Ctrl+D to signal EOF):
  P0

Redirect a file through stdin (full filename including extension required):
  P0 < somefile.fs25s1

Read from a named file (extension .fs25s1 is added automatically):
  P0 somename

------------------------------------------------------------------------
INPUT FORMAT
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tokens are strings of letters and digits separated by any whitespace
(space, tab, newline). Tokens containing other characters produce a
warning on stderr and are skipped.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
OUTPUT
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Three files are written after the tree is built:

  somename.preorder   - preorder traversal  (root, left, right)
  somename.inorder    - inorder traversal   (left, root, right)
  somename.postorder  - postorder traversal (left, right, root)

When no file argument is given, somename is "out".

Each line in the output files:
  <2*depth spaces><frequency>: <token1> <token2> ...

Example output for input "apple banana apple cherry banana apple":
  Preorder:
    3: apple
      2: banana
        1: cherry

------------------------------------------------------------------------
ERROR CONDITIONS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Wrong number of arguments  - prints usage message, exits with code 1
File cannot be opened      - prints error message, exits with code 1

